    {
      "text": "videogioco del 1984\" sviluppato da Nichibutsu",
      "lang": "it",
      "source": "wikidata"
    },
    {
      "text": "Seicross, released as Sector Zone in Japan, is a 1984 isometric shooter video game developed by Alice and published by Nichibutsu for arcades. It was released in Japan in April 1984 and North America in June 1984. A port to the Nintendo Entertainment System was released by Nichibutsu in Japan and FCI in North America in 1986. Hamster Corporation released the game as part of their Arcade Archives series for the Nintendo Switch and PlayStation 4 on June 17, 2021. On April 9, 2026, the home version of the game got ported as part of the Console Archives series.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "『セクターゾーン』 (Sector Zone) は、1984年7月から稼動した日本物産のアーケードゲームである。\n北米版の名称および1986年に発売されたファミリーコンピュータ（およびNES版）への移植版は『セクロス』 (Seicross)となっている。\nファミリーコンピュータ版は後にWindows用のプロジェクトEGGおよびPlayStation 5とNintendo Switch2のコンソールアーカイブスにて配信されている。また、かつてはWii、Wii Uのバーチャルコンソールでも配信されていた。\nアーケード移植版は2021年にアーケードアーカイブスの1作品としてPlayStation 4とNintendo Switchで配信。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "wikipedia_ja"
    },
    {
      "text": "《霹雳机车》（日版名：セクターゾーン，英文版名：Seicross）是一款由日本物產公司制作的街机游戏。游戏后于1986年移植至FC游戏机。\n在游戏中，玩家驾驶着一辆滑翔式的摩托车。游戏目的是撞击别的车手，收集能量模组和收集蓝色搁浅车手。",
      "lang": "zh",
      "source": "wikipedia_zh"
    },
    {
      "text": "Seicross, in Giappone Sector Zero (セクターゾーン?), è un videogioco arcade sviluppato e pubblicato da Nichibutsu nel 1984. Il videogioco è stato convertito per Nintendo Entertainment System e successivamente distribuito per Wii e Wii U tramite Virtual Console.",
      "lang": "it",
      "source": "wikipedia_it"
    },
    {
      "text": "Seicross, é um jogo eletrônico de arcade desenvolvido no Japão pela empresa Nichibutsu, lançado em 1984, com o gênero corrida. Conhecido no Japão como Sector Zero, o videogame foi portado para o Nintendo Entertainment System (NES) e posteriormente lançado para Wii e Wii U através do Virtual Console.",
      "lang": "pt",
      "source": "wikipedia_pt"
    }
  ]
